{{notability|date=September 2011}} {{Infobox software | Kazehakase | name = Kazehakase | logo = [[Image:Kz-logo.png|center|120px]] | screenshot = [[Image:Kazehakase on Ubuntu.png|center|290px]]<!-- See [[Wikipedia:Software screenshots]] --> | released = {{initial release|2003|01|29}} | frequently_updated = yes<!-- Release version update? Don't edit this page, just click on the version number! --> | caption = Screenshot of Kazehakase | operating_system = [[Unix-like]] | genre = [[Web browser]] | license = [[GNU General Public License]] v2 | website = [http://kazehakase.sourceforge.jp/ Kazehakase on sourceforge] }} '''Kazehakase''' ([[Japanese language|Japanese]]: {{lang|ja|é¢¨åå£«}}) is a [[web browser]] for [[Unix-like]] operating systems that uses the [[GTK+]] libraries. Kazehakase embeds the [[Gecko (layout engine)|Gecko layout engine]] as well as GTK+ [[WebKit]]. However, the author also plans to add the ability to switch between additional different rendering engines (e.g. [[GtkHTML]], [[Dillo]], [[w3m]]).{{Citation needed|date=May 2010}} The browser is named after the short story ''Kazehakase'' by [[Japan]]ese author [[Sakaguchi Ango]]. Kazehakase is [[free software]] available under the [[GNU General Public License]].
==Features== Notable features include: *Support for [[RSS (file format)|RSS]] as well as its Japanese variants [[LIRS (standard)|LIRS]] and [[HINA-DI]]<ref>{{cite web|title=About Kazehakase|url=http://kazehakase.sourceforge.jp/?date=20031201|publisher=[[Sourceforge]]|accessdate=1 June 2010|date=May 23, 2010}}</ref> *[[Drag-and-drop]] of [[tab (GUI)|browser tabs]] *[[Mouse gesture]]s *Import of [[Internet bookmark|bookmarks]] from [[Mozilla Firefox]], [[Mozilla Application Suite]], [[Netscape Browser]], [[Galeon]], [[Konqueror]], and [[w3m]]; ''shared bookmarks'' (with [[XBEL]]) *"[[Smart Bookmark]]s" programmable with [[regular expression]]s *[[Full text search]] in browser history
